A job applicant, John Mallum, has been arraigned at an Ogudu Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State for allegedly stealing belongings valued at N645,000. The 20-year-old applicant, who lives at Gbagada, Lagos, was charged on two counts of burglary and stealing, but he pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Inspector Lucky Ihiehie said the defendant committed the offences at Ramat Olukemi Street, Medina Estate, Gbagada, on October 10. He alleged that the defendant broke into the apartment of the complainant, Mrs. Adenike Laja, and stole a Nigerian international passport valued at N80, 000, which contained a British visa valued at N200,000. Ihiehie alleged that Mallum also stole a gold wristwatch worth N120, 000, an HP monitor valued at N40,000, a Blackberry phone worth N130, 000,  five pieces of cloth valued at N25,000 and waterbed mattress worth N50,000. He told the court that the complainant, who caught the defendant as he came out of her apartment, raised the alarm, but the defendant ran away. Magistrate Mrs. Ejiro Kubeinje granted the defendant N100,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. She said that the sureties must be employed and have evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government. The case was adjourned for trial.